text: Pavetta tarennoides is a species of plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is endemic to Kenya. ==Sources== * World Conservation Monitoring Centre 1998. Pavetta tarennoides. 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Downloaded on 23 August 2007.
